g101.definition: [ἀδυνατέω] from {{g102}}; to be unable, i.e. (passively) impossible

g102.definition: [ἀδύνατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1415}}; unable, i.e. weak (literally or figuratively); passively, impossible

g104.definition: [ἀεί] from an obsolete primary noun (apparently meaning continued duration); "ever," by qualification regularly; by implication, earnestly

g105.definition: [ἀετός] from the same as {{g109}}; an eagle (from its wind-like flight)

g106.definition: [ἄζυμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2219}}; unleavened, i.e. (figuratively) uncorrupted; (in the neutral plural) specially (by implication) the Passover week

g107.definition: [Ἀζώρ] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h5809}}); Azor, an Israelite

g108.definition: [Ἄζωτος] of Hebrew origin ({{h795}}); Azotus (i.e. Ashdod), a place in Palestine

g109.definition: [ἀήρ] from ἄημι (to breathe unconsciously, i.e. respire; by analogy, to blow); "air" (as naturally circumambient) Compare {{g5594}}.

g110.definition: [ἀθανασία] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2288}}; deathlessness

g111.definition: [ἀθέμιτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of θέμις (statute; from the base of {{g5087}}); illegal; by implication, flagitious

g112.definition: [ἄθεος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2316}}; godless

g113.definition: [ἄθεσμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5087}} (in the sense of enacting); lawless, i.e. (by implication) criminal

g114.definition: [ἀθετέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5087}}; to set aside, i.e. (by implication) to disesteem, neutralize or violate

g116.definition: [Ἀθῆναι] plural of Ἀθήνη (the goddess of wisdom, who was reputed to have founded the city); Athenæ, the capitol of Greece

g117.definition: [Ἀθηναῖος] from {{g116}}; an Athenæan or inhabitant of Athenæ

g118.definition: [ἀθλέω] from ἄθλος (a contest in the public lists); to contend in the competitive games

g120.definition: [ἀθυμέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2372}}; to be spiritless, i.e. disheartened

g121.definition: [ἄθωος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and probably a derivative of {{g5087}} (meaning a penalty); not guilty

g122.definition: [αἴγειος] from αἴξ (a goat); belonging to a goat

g123.definition: [αἰγιαλός] from aisso (to rush) and {{g251}} (in the sense of the sea); a beach (on which the waves dash)

g124.definition: [Αἰγύπτιος] from {{g125}}; an Ægyptian or inhabitant of Ægyptus

g125.definition: [Αἴγυπτος] of uncertain derivation; Ægyptus, the land of the Nile

g126.definition: [ἀΐδιος] from {{g104}}; everduring (forward and backward, or forward only)

g127.definition: [αἰδώς] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1492}} (through the idea of downcast eyes); bashfulness, i.e. (towards men), modesty or (towards God) awe

g128.definition: [Αἰθίοψ] from αἴθω (to scorch) and ὤψ (the face, from {{g3700}}); an Æthiopian (as a blackamoor)

g129.definition: [αἷμα] of uncertain derivation; blood, literally (of men or animals), figuratively (the juice of grapes) or specially (the atoning blood of Christ); by implication, bloodshed, also kindred

g130.definition: [αἱματεκχυσία] from {{g129}} and a derivative of {{g1632}}; an effusion of blood

g131.definition: [αἱμοῤῥέω] from {{g129}} and {{g4482}}; to flow blood, i.e. have a hæmorrhage

g132.definition: [Αἰνέας] of uncertain derivation; Ænĕas, an Israelite

g133.definition: [αἴνεσις] from {{g134}}; a praising (the act), i.e. (specially) a thank(-offering)

g135.definition: [αἴνιγμα] from a derivative of {{g136}} (in its primary sense); an obscure saying ("enigma"), i.e. (abstractly) obscureness

g136.definition: [αἶνος] apparently a prime word; properly, a story, but used in the sense of {{g1868}}; praise (of God)

g137.definition: [Αἰνών] of Hebrew origin (a derivative of {{h5869}}, place of springs); Ænon, a place in Palestine

g138.definition: [αἱρέομαι] probably akin to {{g142}}; to take for oneself, i.e. to prefer Some of the forms are borrowed from a cognate ἕλλομαι; which is otherwise obsolete.

g139.definition: [αἵρεσις] from {{g138}}; properly, a choice, i.e. (specially) a party or (abstractly) disunion

g140.definition: [αἱρετίζω] from a derivative of {{g138}}; to make a choice

g141.definition: [αἱρετικός] from the same as {{g140}}; a schismatic

g142.definition: [αἴρω] a primary root; to lift up; by implication, to take up or away; figuratively, to raise (the voice), keep in suspense (the mind), specially, to sail away (i.e. weigh anchor); by Hebraism (compare {{h5375}}) to expiate sin

g143.definition: [αἰσθάνομαι] of uncertain derivation; to apprehend (properly, by the senses)

g145.definition: [αἰσθητήριον] from a derivative of {{g143}}; properly, an organ of perception, i.e. (figuratively) judgment

g149.definition: [αἰσχρόν] neuter of {{g150}}; a shameful thing, i.e. indecorum

g150.definition: [αἰσχρός] from the same as {{g153}}; shameful, i.e. base (specially, venal)

g152.definition: [αἰσχύνη] from {{g153}}; shame or disgrace (abstractly or concretely)

g153.definition: [αἰσχύνομαι] from αἶσχος (disfigurement, i.e. disgrace); to feel shame (for oneself)

g154.definition: [αἰτέω] of uncertain derivation; to ask (in genitive case) Compare {{g4441}}.

g155.definition: [αἴτημα] from {{g154}}; a thing asked or (abstractly) an asking

g156.definition: [αἰτία] from the same as {{g154}}; a cause (as if asked for), i.e. (logical) reason (motive, matter), (legal) crime (alleged or proved)

g157.definition: [αἰτίαμα] from a derivative of {{g156}}; a thing charged

g158.definition: [αἴτιον] neuter of {{g159}}; a reason or crime (like {{g156}})

g159.definition: [αἴτιος] from the same as {{g154}}; causative, i.e. (concretely) a causer

g160.definition: [αἰφνίδιος] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5316}} (compare {{g1810}}) (meaning non-apparent); unexpected, i.e. (adverbially) suddenly

g164.definition: [αἰχμάλωτος] from αἰχμή (a spear) and a derivative of the same as {{g259}}; properly, a prisoner of war, i.e. (genitive case) a captive

g165.definition: [αἰών] from the same as {{g104}}; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity (also past); by implication, the world; specially (Jewish) a Messianic period (present or future) Compare {{g5550}}.

g166.definition: [αἰώνιος] from {{g165}}; perpetual (also used of past time, or past and future as well)

g167.definition: [ἀκαθαρσία] from {{g169}}; impurity (the quality), physically or morally

g169.definition: [ἀκάθαρτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2508}} (meaning cleansed); impure (ceremonially, morally (lewd) or specially, (demonic))

g170.definition: [ἀκαιρέομαι] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2540}} (meaning unseasonable); to be inopportune (for oneself), i.e. to fail of a proper occasion

g171.definition: [ἀκαίρως] adverb from the same as {{g170}}; inopportunely

g172.definition: [ἄκακος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2556}}; not bad, i.e. (objectively) innocent or (subjectively) unsuspecting

g173.definition: [ἄκανθα] probably from the same as {{g188}}; a thorn

g175.definition: [ἄκαρπος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2590}}; barren (literally or figuratively)

g176.definition: [ἀκατάγνωστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2607}}; unblamable

g177.definition: [ἀκατακάλυπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of {{g2596}} and {{g2572}}; unveiled

g178.definition: [ἀκατάκριτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2632}}; without (legal) trial

g179.definition: [ἀκατάλυτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2647}}; indissoluble, i.e. (figuratively) permanent

g180.definition: [ἀκατάπαυστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2664}}; unrefraining

g182.definition: [ἀκατάστατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2525}}; inconstant

g183.definition: [ἀκατάσχετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2722}}; unrestrainable

g184.definition: [Ἀκελδαμά] of Chaldee origin (meaning field of blood; corresponding to {{h2506}} and {{h1818}}); Akeldama, a place near Jerusalem

g185.definition: [ἀκέραιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2767}}; unmixed, i.e. (figuratively) innocent

g186.definition: [ἀκλινής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2827}}; not leaning, i.e. (figuratively) firm

g187.definition: [ἀκμάζω] from the same as {{g188}}; to make a point, i.e. (figuratively) mature

g188.definition: [ἀκμήν] accusative case of a noun ("acme") akin to ἀκή (a point) and meaning the same; adverbially, just now, i.e. still

g189.definition: [ἀκοή] from {{g191}}; hearing (the act, the sense or the thing heard)

g190.definition: [ἀκολουθέω] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and κέλευθος (a road); properly, to be in the same way with, i.e. to accompany (specially, as a disciple)

g191.definition: [ἀκούω] a primary verb; to hear (in various senses)

g193.definition: [ἀκρατής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2904}}; powerless, i.e. without self-control

g194.definition: [ἄκρατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2767}}; undiluted

g196.definition: [ἀκριβέστατος] superlative of ἀκρίβης (a derivative of the same as {{g206}}); most exact

g197.definition: [ἀκριβέστερον] neuter of the comparative of the same as {{g196}}; (adverbially) more exactly

g198.definition: [ἀκριβόω] from the same as {{g196}}; to be exact, i.e. ascertain

g199.definition: [ἀκριβῶς] adverb from the same as {{g196}}; exactly

g200.definition: [ἀκρίς] apparently from the same as {{g206}}; a locust (as pointed, or as lighting on the top of vegetation)
